# cmd-ctrl-d natively opens the Dictionary app for the word under the cursor,
# which is not something you can override in native macOS settings. Consume that
# combo so the Dictionary popup never fires, and forward it to a spare hotkey
# (cmd-ctrl-shift-d, the Hammerspoon `hyper` modifier) that Hammerspoon binds
# and acts on. Using `|` (forward) rather than `->` (passthrough) is what
# actually suppresses the Dictionary lookup.
cmd + ctrl - d | cmd + ctrl + shift - d
